  <prompt>
    Patch the NU1903 HIGH-severity vulnerability on `Microsoft.Kiota.Abstractions 1.21.2` (GHSA-7j59-v9qr-6fq9), confirmed at pipeline pre-flight. CRITICAL: per `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md` all Kiota packages MUST stay version-matched. This task may require a chain-coordinated upgrade of multiple Kiota packages — verify before edit.

    Tier: MEDIUM (csproj edit on same major) — owner sign-off + AI-directed verification (adr-check + code-review) per revised NFR-08 (2026-05-24).
  </prompt>

  <role>Security-aware .NET developer + Kiota chain familiarity.</role>

  <goal>Build no longer warns NU1903 on Kiota packages. Tests pass. 24-48h bake passes. Test pass count within ±5% baseline.</goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="csproj">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Sprk.Bff.Api.csproj</file>
    <file purpose="vulnerable">projects/sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix/inventory/vulnerable.txt</file>
    <file purpose="candidates">projects/sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix/CANDIDATES.md</file>
    <file purpose="claude">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md">All Kiota packages MUST stay version-matched at one version</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec.md §Out of Scope">No Kiota individual bumps — chain-coordinated only</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-08 revised 2026-05-24">Owner sign-off + AI-directed verification (adr-check + code-review at task-execute Step 9.5) + CI guards (FR-C1–C6) for MEDIUM/HIGH tier; dual-approver pattern NOT used</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix/inventory/vulnerable.txt</file>
