      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>NU1903 reference: GHSA-7j59-v9qr-6fq9. Kiota chain-lock means bumping Microsoft.Kiota.Abstractions in isolation will likely break the Graph SDK / Kiota generators chain — confirm what other Kiota packages need to move in lockstep before any commit.</background>
    <dependencies><dependency task="037" status="not-started">Phase 3 BASELINE.md</dependency><dependency task="022" status="not-started">CANDIDATES.md MEDIUM tier confirmed</dependency></dependencies>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read CLAUDE.md Kiota chain-lock notes</step>
    <step order="2">Identify all Kiota packages in csproj (`Microsoft.Kiota.*`)</step>
    <step order="3">Research compatible target version that resolves GHSA-7j59-v9qr-6fq9 across the chain</step>
    <step order="4">Cross-reference with Dependabot PRs (any that propose Kiota bumps?)</step>
    <step order="5">Owner acks the chain-coordinated bump plan (NFR-08 revised: operator-only)</step>
    <step order="6">Single commit bumping ALL Kiota packages in lockstep + Microsoft.Graph if chain requires</step>
    <step order="7">build + test (within ±5% baseline)</step>
    <step order="8">Deploy to dev; smoke test; 24-48h bake</step>
    <step order="9">Re-run vuln scan: NU1903 entry resolved (no HIGH on Kiota Abstractions)</step>
    <step order="10">Log to EXECUTION-LOG.md; mark ✅</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">build, test, publish, list package --vulnerable</tool>
    <tool name="powershell">Deploy-BffApi.ps1</tool>
    <tool name="gh">Cross-ref Dependabot PRs</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
